<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Bolgor on 12-14-2001 02:40 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Refferring to the person who said they mostly play a non-cleric and sometimes go without any res... I cannot recall a single time when I died with one of my non-cleric alts and looked for a res. With my non-cleric alts I eat xp deaths for breakfast. I know what its like to be dragged out of a group and across 3 zones to do a res, and I never want to put anyone thru that. XP can be hunted if lost. An hour of running zoning and ressing can never be returned.

Personally as much as i hate doing those out of the way resses, I try to do them as often as possible. Alot of cleric I know go /roleplay or /anon to avoid being botherred. Since I was 30, I have never hidden my cleric tag except by acident once or twice. I made all those levels to be able to do resses, and now that I'm 56... rezzing is what defines my class.

Sometimes people are ungrateful and I don't get a donation or a get the infamous, 12pp 48gp 100sp and a "Sorry, thats all I got" to which I cancel the trade and let them keep it. When people "forget" to donate I ask them if they were planning to, and if they say they didn't then I just remember not to res them next time. 

On the other hand there are some donations I've got for doing resses I'd never want to have missed. I got a Crystalline Eye, 2 forest loops, 2 diamonds, 4 spells, and how many hundreds of plat I couldn't count. When some people profusely thank me for a res, I just answer with, "Its my job." 

And it is... but you have to remember,

Its a job I expect to be paid to do.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
